1]]\n\n''' Juventus '''<ref name=soccerway.com/>\n* [[Serie A]] (5): [[2014\u201315 Serie A|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Serie A|2015\u201316]], [[2016\u201317 Serie A|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Serie A|2017\u201318]], [[2018\u201319 Serie A|2018\u201319]]\n* [[Coppa Italia]] (4): [[2014\u201315 Coppa Italia|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Coppa Italia|2015\u201316]], [[2016\u201317 Coppa Italia|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Coppa Italia|2017\u201318]]\n* [[Supercoppa Italiana]] (2): [[2015 Supercoppa Italiana|2015]], [[2018 Supercoppa Italiana|2018]]\n* [[UEFA Champions League]] Runner-up: [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|2014\u201315]], [[2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League|2016\u201317]] <!-- hold -->\n\n=== Individual ===\n* Panchina d'Oro Prima Divisione (1): [[2007\u201308 Serie C1|2007\u201308]]<ref name=uefa.com/>\n* [[Panchina d'Oro]] (4): [[2008\u201309 Serie A|2008\u201309]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/52242/allegri%E2%80%99s-opportunity-juve%E2%80%99s-gain|title=Allegri\u2019s opportunity, Juve\u2019s gain?|publisher=Football Italia|date=17 July 2014|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref> [[2014\u201315 Serie A|2014\u201315]],<ref name=juvepanchia/> [[2016\u201317 Serie A|2016\u201317]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/119041/allegri-wins-2017-panchina-doro|title=Allegri wins 2017 Panchina d\u2019Oro|publisher=Football Italia|date=26 March 2018|accessdate=26 March 2018}}</ref> [[2017\u201318 Serie A|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2018/allegri-named-best-manager-in-italy-for-the-fourth-time.php|title=Allegri named best manager in Italy for the fourth time!|publisher=juventus.com|date=12 November 2018|accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Serie A Coach of the Year]] (4): [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2011]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/9383781/serie-a-juventus-appoint-massimiliano-allegri-as-new-coach|title=Serie A: Juventus appoint Massimiliano Allegri as new coach|publisher=Sky Sports|date=16 July 2014|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref> [[2014\u201315 Serie A|2015]],<ref name=\"Sport Mediaset\"/> [[2015\u201316 Serie A|2016]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2017/01/30/gran-gala-del-calcio-2017-premiati.html|title=Gran Gal\u00e0 del calcio, la notte delle stelle|publisher=Sky.it|language=Italian|date=30 January 2017|accessdate=31 January 2017}}</ref> [[2017\u201318 Serie A|2018]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/131572/allegri-wins-serie-coach-year|title=Allegri wins Serie A Coach of the Year|publisher=Football Italia|date=3 December 2018|accessdate=3 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Enzo Bearzot Award]] (1): 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivoazzurro.it/en/figcnews/e-allegri-il-vincitore-del-premio-bearzot-la-premiazione-il-25-maggio-al-coni-2/|title=Allegri wins Bearzot award|publisher=Vivo Azzurro|date=25 March 2015|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[IFFHS World's Best Club Coach]]: 2015 (third place),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/detail/article/leo-messi-and-luis-enrique-honoured-by-iffhs|title=Leo Messi and Luis Enrique honoured by IFFHS|publisher=FC Barcelona|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref> 2017 (second place)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/detail/article/leo-messi-and-luis-enrique-honoured-by-iffhs|title=Leo Messi and Luis Enrique honoured by IFFHS|publisher=FC Barcelona|accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref>\n* [[The Best FIFA Football Coach#Men.27s winners|The Best FIFA Men's Coach]]: [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2017#The Best FIFA Men.27s Coach|2017]] (third place)<ref name=\"2017 The Best FIFA Men's Coach\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/best-fifa-mens-coach/index.html|title=The Best FIFA Men's Coach|publisher=FIFA.com|accessdate=23 October 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Gazzetta Sports Awards]] \u2013 Coach of the Year: 2018<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www